cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Nevertwice in your work or research, please cite it."
title: "Nevertwice: Local-first long-term memory for AI coding agents"
abstract: >-
  A local-first, zero-dependency agent-memory system that stores distilled lessons
  as plain Markdown under git, with hybrid local-embedding + lexical retrieval,
  calibrated abstention, bi-temporal supersession, and a measured, honest account
  of which memory-ranking mechanisms actually help on real data.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Chernov
    given-names: Platon
repository-code: "https://github.com/DonPlaton/nevertwice"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - agent-memory
  - long-term-memory
  - retrieval-augmented-generation
  - large-language-models
  - local-first
  - llm-agents
